name: In the heart of the city
description: Guests are usually greeted with a warm welcome and introduction to the city by me personally. Guests love the proximity to city centre and all public transport. They also enjoy the vibrant multicultural life with affordable dining options on the footsteps.
neighborhood_overview:
Grønland - District in Oslo
In lively, multicultural Greenland, there are many shops with food from the Middle East and restaurants that sell kebabs and børek. Informal venues serving curries, laid-back pubs and lively dance clubs can also be found in the area. And nearby is Oslo Spektrum, a huge indoor arena where there are often concerts with great artists. Greenland Bazaar is a small shopping center in the middle of Greenland, and not far away is Oslo City, a large shopping center with many different shops.
host_about:
Welcome to my home. 

Over the past 10 years I have hosted thousands of fellow earthlings from all over Gaia and come to know many of them and their cultures. 

It is incredibly inspirational being a host and I feel the world is coming closer as one with greater respect and understanding for each other.

Not surprisingly, I also love to travel, meet new people and their cultures but until now I have mostly only traveled in the far east and I have not yet crossed the dam.

If you desire I will also spend time with you, socializing and showing you the city. Use me as a guide or someone just to hang out with :)

“A journey of a thousand miles must begin with a single step.” 老子

name: Lovely bedroom in beautiful area.
description: Peaceful doublebedroom, facing quiet and green backyard, located in lovely old neighbourhood with beautiful architecture,  five minutes walk from the Vigeland sculpturepark- five minutes walk away from the Royal Castle.  We use all ecological detergents for bed linen and towels, soaps, shampoos and dish washing soaps. Busses, trams run just outside. Bring your jogging outfit and have a lovely run among the Vigeland sculptures. We´ll provide our best sightseeing recommandations.
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighbourhod is lovely and quiet. There are lots of old trees, beautiful architecture and nice cafes. You are five minutes walk away from The Vigelands sculpture park. The Royal Castle and the lovely park around that is five minutes away. In the morning, you should try out our wonderful breakfast cafe ÅPENT BAKERI. They have a wonderful sourdough bread, freshly made jam, a great atmosphere inside, and open at 7.30. In the summertime they have the nicest outdoor space, under the flower trees. You could have a morning and night swim in Tjuvholmen outdoor bath. There is also the Thief Spa, and it´s a lovely place to hang out and contemplate. Parks and waterfrontbenches among the beautiful living space. Also the gallery Astrup Fearnley has a great collection of contemporary arts, and impressive architecture. Olivia restaurant, on the waterfront at sunset is also adorable. The Italian icecream-shop, a must.
The Litterature house is within walking distance, a great space with a boo
host_about:
I'm a filmmaker and  have been living in the apartment with my daughter for eighteen years. Lovisa just moved out but the cat Chagall and I are still around, loving our home and our guests.  I rent a lovely double bedroom in our calm and safe neighborhood right behind the Royal Palace within walking distance to most sights. You access the shared bathroom from your bedroom and we share my well equipped, sit in kitchen.
Welcome!❤️

description:
5-room Modern Apt, for 9 persons; situated in a unique area i.e
the heart of the city, yet it is very homely. A newly built apt. Just few minutes walk from Oslo central station, close walking distance to Gardens, walking distance to everything centrally. Bus service 24 hrs .Great eat out places.
